# Challenge Overview > List of Challenges

See below for the list of challenge lessons. Feel free to click through to the lesson plans and explore the materials so you can select one to complete. **Your goal right now is to pick the lesson that you will complete later.**

*As you review these challenge topics, you will notice that there are a few that have a lot of levels- note that you don't need to complete every single level of the lessons. Instead, focus your energy on the topics that are new to you, and do as much as you feel you need to do to understand the concepts.*

## Are you fairly new to programming? Pick one of these…

### Lessons 2 - 5: Turtle Drawing

**Consider doing if:** You are totally new to programming.

**Lesson Plans:** <a href=”https://docs.google.com/document/d/1TL3j0pcKHvpAruyoqpIb5a84vyMCRm8el20y6Ck6pTk/edit” target =_blank>Lesson 2: Using Simple Commands >></a>
| <a href=”https://docs.google.com/document/d/1Q7j0s0z04ykJoS6gu096QjJOuUYt4jbbz7GxNz1UeVs/edit” target =_blank>Lesson 3: Creating Functions >></a>
| <a href=”https://docs.google.com/document/d/1uw4yg-1EI5thSMBGnFIgH-VGuF3OKNEDJcWXVvq_CFM/edit” target =_blank>Lesson 4: Functions and Top-Down Design >></a>
 | <a href=”https://docs.google.com/document/d/1x0XymE9nEEQkVoOED53Wwu3ssBpcJEFESv-K4RInUa4/edit” target =_blank>Lesson 5: APIs and Function Parameters >></a>

>**You will learn:** These lessons teach simple programming commands, turtle drawing, reading the documentation that describes what a programming language can do. 

>**You will produce:** A drawing using turtle functions that you learned about in the documentation.

>**You will share:** The program you create on <a href="https://studio.code.org/s/cspunit3/lessons/5/levels/10" target=_blank>Stage 5, level 10.</a>

### Lessons 6 - 7: Functions and Simple Loops

**Consider doing if:** You have some experience with programming, but want to brush up on some of the basics. 

**Lesson Plans:** <a href=”https://docs.google.com/document/d/13b3z3Zg7S78X6FKfEqI4q7y2kQx9bLc1MAyGUjEQfi0/edit” target =_blank>Lesson 6: Creating Functions with Parameters >></a>
 | <a href=”https://docs.google.com/document/d/1PBPLJ-qFkXrFuVo4MdsRC081rntY1mLyQTBQGtHJDvI/edit” target =_blank>Lesson 7: Looping and Random Numbers >></a>

>**You will learn:** These lessons teach the creation of functions that take an input when they’re used (called functions with parameters), simple repeat loops, and how to create random numbers in a program. 

>**You will produce:** A drawing of an ocean scene that looks slightly different each time you run the program, with randomly generated numbers of fish and other ocean friends.

>**You will share:** The program you create on <a href="https://studio.code.org/s/cspunit3/lessons/7/levels/11" target=_blank>Stage 7, level 11.</a>

